Title: Intro to CSP report-to and report-uri HTTP headers
Description:
CSP Directives: report-to and report-uri The Content Security Policy (CSP) directives report-to and report-uri are used to specify where the browser should send violation reports when a content security policy is violated on a website.
Why Use Them:
Helps in identifying and fixing security issues on a website. Provides insights into potential attacks or vulnerabilities. Enhances the overall security posture of the website. PCI Compliance report-uri - CSP Directive Legacy CSP directive that is used for reporting violations Deprecated but not all browsers support the newer directives so it is still recommended to be used report-uri Example Content-Security-Policy: .
